    <!-- Rules -->
    <string name="Rules">Rules</string>
    <string name="text">Black always begins the game.\n Then the players play turn by turn, each has to catch the disks of the opponent during his turn.\n If a player can\'t catch an opponent disk, he is forced to pass his turn.\n If none of the players can play,
        or if the Reversi have no empty case left, the game end.\n The winner at the end of the game is the one which process the most disks.\n A catch of a disk happens when a player place one of his disk at the end of the disks alignment of opponent\'s disks and which is ended by one of his own disks.\n The alignments considered are column, line or diagonal.\n If the newly placed disk has closed many alignments, it catches every opponent disks of the lines it closes.\n A catch returns every disks captured.</string>

